From 88a949640e9334d664ab98d15cddc2551b2a370c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 03:14:08 +0200
Subject: slayzone: Phase 6.3 C++ binder scaffold (Option C handoff to 7.x)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Ships only the C++ side of the URL-bar wiring: chrome://slayzone-browserchrome/
and chrome://slayzone-tabbar/ WebUIControllers each bind the Phase 6.1
slayzone::tabs::mojom::TabsHost Mojo interface, forwarding to the owning
SlayzoneBrowserView's SlayzoneTabsHost. JS URL-bar + tab-strip consumers
are deferred to Phases 7.8 + 7.2 per orchestrator call — the plan is that
Phase 6 exit criteria (4 SSO flows, ≥3 extensions, <50ms tab switch) are
measured end-to-end via CDP + programmatic Mojo drives in 6.4 + 6.5,
not via user-facing JS yet.

  - chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_browserchrome_ui.{h,cc}
    new chrome://slayzone-browserchrome/ WebUIController with placeholder
    HTML body + WEB_UI_CONTROLLER_TYPE_DECL/IMPL. `BindInterface(TabsHost)`
    looks up the owning SlayzoneBrowserView via a WebContentsUserData
    back-pointer and forwards the receiver to tabs_host()->Bind().

  - chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_tabbar_ui.{h,cc}
    same shape for chrome://slayzone-tabbar/.

  - chrome/common/webui_url_constants.{h,cc}
    two new host/URL constants; both added to ChromeURLHosts().

  - chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_webui_registry.cc
    registers both configs alongside Shell + Placeholder.

  - chrome/browser/chrome_browser_interface_binders_webui_parts_desktop.cc
    ForWebUI<SlayzoneBrowserchromeUI>().Add<TabsHost>() +
    ForWebUI<SlayzoneTabbarUI>().Add<TabsHost>() binder entries next to
    the TabSearchUI binding.

  - chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/slayzone_browser_view.{h,cc}
    adds `SlayzoneBrowserView::FromRegionWebContents(wc)` static helper
    backed by a private WebContentsUserData (RegionData in an anonymous
    namespace) installed for every region WebView's WebContents in
    AddedToWidget. This is what the WebUIController BindInterface calls
    consult to route Mojo receivers back to the owning view.

  - chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/slayzone_region_container.cc
    RegionUrl() routes browserchrome → kChromeUISlayzoneBrowserchromeURL
    and tabbar → kChromeUISlayzoneTabbarURL; every other slot still points
    at chrome://slayzone-placeholder/<id>.

  - chrome/browser/ui/BUILD.gn
    adds the four new .cc/.h files to the ui static_library sources.
